<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-03T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="288" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/3737: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dennis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-03T14:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">June 3,
                                        1925—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 4—11:15
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>73. Referring to the Department’s telegram of May 29, 5 p.m. The
                            Honduranean Government has sent instructions to Lainez<note n="24" xml:id="d288fn24">Silverio Lainez, Honduran Minister to
                                Guatemala.</note> to make appropriate representations to the
                            Guatemalan Government on the basis of the Ferrera letters, fresh
                            invasions, and the findings of a commission of investigation along the
                            border. …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Guatemala and Salvador.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dennis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>